{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"unbathed-pale-hogget","creation_channel":"python","description":"# Dogfood the completed lifecycle in rebar\n\n## Goal\nProve the integrated behavior through public surfaces and enable both optional policies for this project without requiring migration or backfill.\n\n## Implementation\n- Enable verify.enforce_plan_material_pins and verify.require_plan_review_for_close in rebar.toml; retain false defaults in the reusable configuration schema.\n- Add public-surface lifecycle scenarios for: legacy unpinned attestations; emission while enforcement is off; enable/disable/re-enable; direct child drift; depends_on and blocks normalization; natural A-to-B-to-C transitivity; successful unchanged re-review stopping propagation; execution-time self-edit; in_progress-to-open reset; code-only drift at close; deleted and archived pinned targets; concurrent review/close changes; and audited force-close.\n- Verify no eager backfill, graph-wide invalidation event, new pin command, list-output change, or stored relation migration occurs.\n- Update configuration golden surfaces and release notes as required by project conventions.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Rebar enables both policies while library defaults remain off, and a pre-feature unpinned attestation continues to pass both gates.\n- [ ] End-to-end tests prove direct and natural-transitive invalidation only after actual narrow material changes, including no propagation after an unchanged successful re-review.\n- [ ] Execution adaptation, return-to-open reset, code-only close freshness, toggles, deletion/archive handling, concurrency rechecks, and force-close are proven through public lifecycle surfaces.\n\n## Verification\n- Run the complete lifecycle interface suite with both rebar policies enabled.\n- Run make check and the full non-integration test suite.\n- Run a real review-plan and claim/close dry run on fixture tickets and record the observed gate health on this ticket.\n","id":"145e-52a9-26e3-4209","parent_id":"jira-reb-1160","priority":2,"tags":["plan-review","jira-reb-1160"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Enable material-pin and close-review enforcement for rebar with lifecycle acceptance coverage"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784517384153584001,"uuid":"37084eb5-65af-485e-a328-7b36d76b06b1"}